---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base path="/correspondents" title="Become a correspondent" description="Report from your city for ArtempireMJ. The world, told through the artists who live it, needs eyes on the ground everywhere.">
  <section class="wrap" style="padding-block: clamp(2rem,6vw,4rem) 1rem;">
    <p class="eyebrow">The network</p>
    <h1>Report from your city.</h1>
    <p class="lede prose">The world told through artists needs eyes on the ground, everywhere.
      ArtempireMJ’s correspondents are the people who walk the fair, sit in the studio, and send
      back what only someone there can see. Khethiwe Tracy Gumede reports from South Africa. The
      network grows by city, and the next one could be yours.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap prose" style="padding-block: 1rem 3rem; max-width: 44rem;">
    <h2>What a correspondent does</h2>
    <p class="muted">You cover the art happening where you are. A fair, an opening, a studio visit,
      a maker worth knowing. You send the story and the pictures. We tell the world through it,
      with your name on it.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">What you get</h2>
    <p class="muted">Your byline in front of a growing audience. A masthead behind your work. A real
      rung, the way Khethiwe started: one city, one fair, one story at a time, building from there.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">How to start</h2>
    <p class="muted">Tell us your city and the art you would cover. Choose "I want to report from my
      city" when you write to us.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:1.2rem;"><a class="btn" href="/submit">Write to us</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
